story.title: My Fiance's Brother - Episode 2
story.storyDescription: Taylor is marrying her best friend's brother. But then her best friend confesses he's in love with her...
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: I can‚Äôt ‚Äî we‚Äôre supposed to grow old together.
No. I‚Äôm supposed to grow old with Blake.
The same Blake who cheats on you?
The same man who makes you cry?
He‚Äôs not the one making me cry right now.
I don‚Äôt want you to cry.
How could someone like you be with Blake?
You asked why I chose him.
No. You were full of life.
That‚Äôs not what my parents called it.
They wanted me to focus on the things that mattered.
They don‚Äôt like when I sing at pubs.
Or volunteer at the rescue shelter.
They want you to be more like Blake?
My parents liked him right away.
The day you met my parents, you rode a skateboard to our house.
You were skating downhill in a dress.
I couldn‚Äôt ride that thing in heels.
But you could in a dress.
You wore one, just to impress my parents.
I wanted them to like me.
I wanted Blake to like me, too.
He was captain of the football team‚Äî
You went out with Blake because of your dad?
I knew my parents would like him, too.
They did. Once I started dating him‚Ä¶
I stopped playing guitar in pubs. I joined the Young Republicans‚Äô club.
I didn‚Äôt think it would go that far.
I went from eating at a diner to eating at the club.
And you left the pubs and puppies behind.
Not the puppies ‚Äî never the puppies.
Everyone told me I needed to grow up.
The best way I knew how.
It wasn‚Äôt his fault. We both fell into the trap.
We won Homecoming King and Queen.
I voted for Mark and Henry.
So then you remember that everyone thought Blake and I were the perfect together.
I didn‚Äôt want to believe it.
It hurt too much to believe.
I never meant to hurt you.
I know ‚Äî but it hurts anyway.
As more than just a friend?
I can‚Äôt go there with you.
Yeah. But did you ever want more?
What do want me to say?
That I‚Äôll leave Blake for you?
That you professed your love in the nick of time?
Jesus, how long have you felt this way?
Do you have any idea what you‚Äôre doing to me?
Do you have any idea how much this hurts?
You should have said something, Jonathan.
You should have said something, too.
When? Before your first girlfriend or after your last?
They could have been if you weren‚Äôt with Blake.
That‚Äôs not what it feels like.
It bothered you to see Blake kiss me.
Well it crushed me to see you with all those girls.
Like they couldn‚Äôt wait to crawl into bed with you.
I don‚Äôt want to fight with you.
I just want to love you.
I can‚Äôt get over how bad we screwed up.
When did you realize you had feelings for me?
The first time you showed me your artwork.
Why didn‚Äôt you ever tell me?
All those nights we were up talking?
J, I‚Äôm carrying your brother‚Äôs child!
Or that I love you, too?
I know. I just‚Ä¶damn it. You should have told me.
You should have told me, too‚Ä¶
The next few days pass in a haze for Taylor.
Numb and feeling alone, she walks down the aisle.
Through the translucent fabric of her veil, she sees the man she loves, standing beside the man she‚Äôs marrying.
Her hand skims over her belly as tears soak her cheeks.
Jonathan bows his head. A strand of dark hair from his Mohawk skims the clenching muscles of his jaw.
He takes a breath, his hands balling to fists.
Does anyone object to this union?
